('chunk_3ffdce0fc468d74640','file_c827a0b7bfd97ec469','world-languages.md','Unit 1 — Education and the World of Work','- **Core vocabulary fields:** days of the week; times & telling the time; daily routine verbs (get up, wash, eat, go, study, sleep); school subjects; classroom objects; school places (library, canteen, gym); jobs/professions; family members (as context for routines).
- **Key grammar/structures:** present tense of high-frequency and regular verbs; **reflexive verbs** for routine (get up, wash, get dressed); **question words** (what, when, where, who, why, how, how many); time expressions and sequencers (first, then, after that, finally); **connectors** (and, but, because, also).
- **Target text type — Email/Letter (formal vs informal):**
  - *Informal:* friendly greeting (Hi/Dear + first name), relaxed tone, contractions/colloquial phrases, personal questions, casual sign-off (See you / Bye + name).
  - *Formal:* formal salutation (Dear Sir/Madam / Dear Mr/Ms + surname), clear purpose statement, polite register, no slang, formal closing (Yours sincerely/faithfully + full name).
  - Shared structure: greeting → opening → body (purpose/details) → closing → sign-off.
- **Communicative functions:** greetings & introductions; describing a daily routine; telling the time; asking and answering questions; expressing likes/dislikes about subjects.
- **Command-term tasks:** *Identify* the times in an audio timetable (A); *Respond* to questions about your school day (C); *Describe* your daily routine orally (C/D); *Write* an informal email to a pen-pal about school and a formal email to a teacher (D).','{"unit":1,"education":1,"and":6,"the":5,"world":1,"work":1,"core":1,"vocabulary":1,"fields":1,"days":1,"week":1,"times":2,"telling":2,"time":3,"daily":3,"routine":4,"verbs":3,"get":3,"wash":2,"eat":1,"study":1,"sleep":1,"school":4,"subjects":2,"classroom":1,"objects":1,"places":1,"library":1,"canteen":1,"gym":1,"jobs":1,"professions":1,"family":1,"members":1,"context":1,"for":2,"routines":1,"key":1,"grammar":1,"structures":1,"present":1,"tense":1,"high":1,"frequency":1,"regular":1,"reflexive":1,"dressed":1,"question":1,"words":1,"what":1,"when":1,"where":1,"who":1,"why":1,"how":2,"many":1,"expressions":1,"sequencers":1,"first":2,"then":1,"after":1,"that":1,"finally":1,"connectors":1,"but":1,"because":1,"also":1,"target":1,"text":1,"type":1,"email":3,"letter":1,"formal":5,"informal":3,"friendly":1,"greeting":2,"dear":3,"name":3,"relaxed":1,"tone":1,"contractions":1,"colloquial":1,"phrases":1,"personal":1,"questions":3,"casual":1,"sign":2,"off":2,"see":1,"you":1,"bye":1,"salutation":1,"sir":1,"madam":1,"surname":1,"clear":1,"purpose":2,"statement":1,"polite":1,"register":1,"slang":1,"closing":2,"yours":1,"sincerely":1,"faithfully":1,"full":1,"shared":1,"structure":1,"opening":1,"body":1,"details":1,"communicative":1,"functions":1,"greetings":1,"introductions":1,"describing":1,"asking":1,"answering":1,"expressing":1,"likes":1,"dislikes":1,"about":3,"command":1,"term":1,"tasks":1,"identify":1,"audio":1,"timetable":1,"respond":1,"your":2,"day":1,"describe":1,"orally":1,"write":1,"pen":1,"pal":1,"teacher":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_ef74261c192a117dd4','file_c827a0b7bfd97ec469','world-languages.md','Unit 2 — Technology and the Media','- **Core vocabulary fields:** devices (phone, tablet, laptop, computer); apps & platforms; online actions (post, share, like, comment, chat, download, watch, play); frequency adverbs (always, often, sometimes, never); opinion phrases; time online.
- **Key grammar/structures:** present tense with frequency adverbs; **negation**; verbs of liking/preferring + noun/infinitive; **opinion structures** (I think that…, In my opinion…, I agree/disagree); connectors for contrast (however, on the other hand).
- **Target text type — Social media post:** short and punchy; hook/first line; informal register and emojis; hashtags; a call to interact (like/share/comment); optional image caption. Teach appropriate register and digital-citizenship conventions.
- **Communicative functions:** expressing opinions; agreeing/disagreeing; describing habits & frequency; recommending an app or activity.
