('chunk_e5309cfebfb8a7e364','file_c827a0b7bfd97ec469','world-languages.md','Unit 3 — The World We Live In','- **Core vocabulary fields:** weather expressions; seasons; temperature; nature & landscape (mountain, river, forest, beach); environmental problems (pollution, waste, plastic, climate change); eco-actions (recycle, save water/energy, reuse, plant trees).
- **Key grammar/structures:** weather expressions (impersonal "it is / there is" forms); **near future** to talk about plans/predictions (introduced as a chunk: "going to…"); imperatives for advice/appeals (Recycle! Save water!); comparatives (more/less than); connectors of cause & effect (because, so, therefore).
- **Target text type — Article:** headline; introduction (hook + topic); body organised in paragraphs (problem → cause → solution); facts/examples; conclusion or call to action; may include subheadings. Register is informative and semi-formal.
- **Communicative functions:** describing weather; expressing concern; giving advice/making appeals; presenting facts.
- **Command-term tasks:** *Identify* weather details in a forecast (A); *Present* an environmental problem and solution (C); *Describe* the weather across seasons (D); *Write* a short article encouraging eco-friendly habits (D).','{"unit":1,"the":2,"world":1,"live":1,"core":1,"vocabulary":1,"fields":1,"weather":5,"expressions":2,"seasons":2,"temperature":1,"nature":1,"landscape":1,"mountain":1,"river":1,"forest":1,"beach":1,"environmental":2,"problems":1,"pollution":1,"waste":1,"plastic":1,"climate":1,"change":1,"eco":2,"actions":1,"recycle":2,"save":2,"water":2,"energy":1,"reuse":1,"plant":1,"trees":1,"key":1,"grammar":1,"structures":1,"impersonal":1,"there":1,"forms":1,"near":1,"future":1,"talk":1,"about":1,"plans":1,"predictions":1,"introduced":1,"chunk":1,"going":1,"imperatives":1,"for":1,"advice":2,"appeals":2,"comparatives":1,"more":1,"less":1,"than":1,"connectors":1,"cause":2,"effect":1,"because":1,"therefore":1,"target":1,"text":1,"type":1,"article":2,"headline":1,"introduction":1,"hook":1,"topic":1,"body":1,"organised":1,"paragraphs":1,"problem":2,"solution":2,"facts":2,"examples":1,"conclusion":1,"call":1,"action":1,"may":1,"include":1,"subheadings":1,"register":1,"informative":1,"and":2,"semi":1,"formal":1,"communicative":1,"functions":1,"describing":1,"expressing":1,"concern":1,"giving":1,"making":1,"presenting":1,"command":1,"term":1,"tasks":1,"identify":1,"details":1,"forecast":1,"present":1,"describe":1,"across":1,"write":1,"short":1,"encouraging":1,"friendly":1,"habits":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_4832d73e58bfcbb5e7','file_c827a0b7bfd97ec469','world-languages.md','Unit 4 — Identity and Culture','- **Core vocabulary fields:** foods; drinks; meals (breakfast, lunch, dinner); quantities & containers; flavours & opinions (delicious, sweet, spicy, healthy, unhealthy); body & health (tired, ill, healthy); healthy-habit verbs (eat, drink, sleep, exercise, rest).
- **Key grammar/structures:** likes/dislikes + food nouns; **partitive / quantity expressions** (some, a lot of); **giving advice** with "should" / imperatives (You should eat…, Drink more water!); adjective agreement with food nouns; frequency for habits.
- **Target text type — Brochure:** catchy title; short informative sections with subheadings; bullet points and tips; imperatives and direct address ("you"); persuasive, positive tone; images/layout; contact or call-to-action panel.
- **Communicative functions:** expressing food preferences; ordering/offering food; giving health advice; describing a healthy lifestyle.
- **Command-term tasks:** *Identify* foods and opinions in a dialogue (A); *Respond* in a role-play at a café/market (C); *Describe* your diet and healthy habits (D); *Write* a brochure promoting healthy eating and well-being (D).

