('chunk_ad4671d052cf6ca3b0','file_c827a0b7bfd97ec469','world-languages.md','7. Common Misconceptions — Master List','| Language | Misconception / Error | Correction |
|---|---|---|
| Spanish | *ser/estar* both mean "to be" and are interchangeable | *ser* = permanent/identity; *estar* = location/temporary state |
| Spanish | False friends: *embarazada, librería, éxito, sensible* | pregnant, bookshop, success, sensitive |
| Spanish | *el problema/día* must be feminine (ends in -a) | some -a nouns are masculine; learn gender per noun |
| Spanish | Adjective needn''t agree | agree in gender & number: *la casa blanca* |
| French | Silent letters should be pronounced | many final consonants are silent; observe liaison |
| French | Skip the partitive: *Je mange pain* | use du/de la/des: *Je mange du pain* |
| French | Accents are optional decoration | accents change meaning: *ou/où*, *a/à* |
| French | False friends: *librairie, journée, actuellement* | bookshop, day, currently |
| French | Adjective before noun (English order) | most follow the noun: *une voiture rouge* |
| Hindi | Prepositions before nouns | postpositions after: *स्कूल में* |
| Hindi | Verb needn''t match gender | verb agrees with gender: *मैं खाती हूँ* (f.) |
| Hindi | Use तू with everyone | use आप (+ plural verb) for respect |
| Hindi | Similar letters interchangeable (ब/भ/म; व/ब) | distinct sounds & meanings; watch matras |
| Telugu | Any sandhi rule fits | apply the specific sandhi rule; verify by splitting |
| Telugu | Wrong vibhakti marker | match case marker to the noun''s grammatical role |
| Telugu | Colloquial forms in formal writing | use standard/written register in composition |
| All | Word-for-word translation from English | learn chunks and patterns; respect word order (Hindi/Telugu SOV) |

