('chunk_ad2e012b903329a599','file_c827a0b7bfd97ec469','world-languages.md','8. Task / Question Bank (spanning the four skills)','*(Adapt the same task to Spanish, French or Hindi. Command terms in bold.)*

1. **(Criterion A – Listening)** Listen to a short audio of a student''s daily routine. **Identify** the times of four activities and **state** the person''s favourite subject.
2. **(Criterion B – Reading)** Read a social-media post about screen time. **Identify** two opinions the writer expresses and **explain** whether they are for or against limiting screen time.
3. **(Criterion C – Speaking/Interaction)** In pairs, role-play ordering food and drink at a café. **Respond** appropriately, express a preference, and ask one question. (Unit 4)
4. **(Criterion C – Speaking)** **Present** a 60–90 second talk describing the weather across the four seasons where you live. (Unit 3)
5. **(Criterion D – Writing)** **Write** a formal email to a school principal requesting to join a club, and an informal email to a friend about the same club — showing you can switch register. (Unit 1)
6. **(Criterion D – Writing)** **Write** a short brochure (title, 2 sections, tips, call to action) promoting healthy eating and well-being to teenagers. (Unit 4)
7. **(Criterion B + D)** Read a model article on recycling, then **write** your own short article that **describes** an environmental problem and **suggests** two solutions. (Unit 3)
8. **(Telugu – Language & Literature)** Read the assigned prose lesson. **Identify** the central value it teaches, **explain** it with one example from the text, and **write** a short reflective paragraph on how you apply that value.

