('chunk_542baa50bb87a6931d','file_c827a0b7bfd97ec469','world-languages.md','9. Cross-Subject Connections','- **Individuals & Societies:** geography of weather/climate and the environment (Unit 3); world of work and economics (Unit 1); cultures and identity (Unit 4).
- **Sciences:** climate change, pollution and sustainability (Unit 3); nutrition, health and the body (Unit 4); technology and its effects (Unit 2).
- **Design / Digital Citizenship:** creating a social-media post, brochure and article — layout, audience, purpose, responsible online behaviour (Units 2, 4).
- **Language & Literature (and Telugu):** shared concepts of audience, purpose, form, register and text-type conventions transfer across all languages; comparing structures builds metalinguistic awareness.
- **Arts:** poetry recitation, food/cultural expression, poster and brochure design.
- **Physical & Health Education:** well-being, healthy habits and balanced lifestyle (Unit 4).
- **Service as Action / IB Learner Profile:** environmental appeals (Unit 3) and healthy-living campaigns (Unit 4) connect to *caring, principled, communicators*; intercultural understanding across all languages develops *open-minded* learners.

